title: How to Grow Houseplants From Clippings
summary: Houseplants can provide wonderful and healthy additions to your home, but filling your house with them can get expensive quickly if you buy them fully grown from a nursery. An alternative is to learn how to grow houseplants from clippings taken from your existing plants. Plants are capable of reproducing asexually if they have been cut, as the cut tissue will begin forming a new root in a hospitable environment. Growing new plants from cuttings is a simple process, but does require careful oversight to ensure the health of your new houseplant.
